). Pygidial papilla present.

Dorsal cirri of median segments rounded cordate, symmetrical, about as long as wide (
Fig. 28D–H
). Dorsal cirrophores small, dorsally indistinct. Neuropodium with supra-acicular lobes longer than subacicular lobes, with 12–15 chaetae. Dorsal and ventral chaetae similar within single fascicle. Rostrum of chaetal shaft asymmetrical, with single large main tooth on anterior side (
Fig. 37G
). Ventral cirri oval, slightly shorter than neuropodia. Pygidial cirri oval 1.5–2 times as long as wide (
Fig. 27E
). Pygidial papilla present.

